      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@AdamGent The question was asked at a time when Spring 3.2 was not yet released.  Go back and take a look at the JavaDoc for 3.1, and you will notice there is no such mention of utilizing <code>@RequestParam</code> on a <code>Map&lt;String,String&gt;</code> to retrieve all query string parameters.  And please, don&#39;t feel <b><i>so</i></b> abhorred over the answers you see here...they aren&#39;t <b><i>that</i></b> bad :)  <a href=\"http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.1.x/javadoc-api/org/springframework/web/bind/annotation/RequestParam.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.1.x/javadoc-api/org/&hellip;</a>"
