    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>While the other answers are correct it certainly is not the &quot;Spring way&quot; to use the HttpServletRequest object directly. The answer is actually <a href=\"http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.2.x/javadoc-api/org/springframework/web/bind/annotation/RequestParam.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">quite simple and what you would expect</a> if you're familiar with Spring MVC.</p>\n<pre><code>@RequestMapping(value = {&quot;/search/&quot;, &quot;/search&quot;}, method = RequestMethod.GET)\npublic String search(\n@RequestParam Map&lt;String,String&gt; allRequestParams, ModelMap model) {\n   return &quot;viewName&quot;;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
