    "answer_id" : 48497713,
    "question_id" : 7312436,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Here's a simple example of <strong>getting <code>requestParams</code> in a <code>Map</code>:</strong></p>\n<pre><code>@RequestMapping(value=&quot;submitForm.html&quot;, method=RequestMethod.POST)\npublic ModelAndView submitForm(@RequestParam Map&lt;String, String&gt; reqParam) {\n    String name  = reqParam.get(&quot;studentName&quot;);\n    String email = reqParam.get(&quot;studentEmail&quot;);     \n    ModelAndView model = new ModelAndView(&quot;AdmissionSuccess&quot;);\n    model.addObject(&quot;msg&quot;, &quot;Details submitted by you::Name: &quot; + name\n                                                + &quot;, Email: &quot; + email );\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>In this case, it will bind the values:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>studentName</code> with <code>name</code></li>\n<li><code>studentEmail</code> with <code>email</code></li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
